# Client Management Feature - Product Requirements Document
## Anya Segen Knowledge Management System

**Version**: 1.0  
**Date**: January 2025  
**Feature**: Client Management Module  
**Integration**: Next.js 15 + Supabase + TypeScript

---

## 1. Executive Summary

The Client Management feature will extend the existing Anya Segen platform to handle comprehensive client (politician/corporate) information management. This module will integrate seamlessly with the current role-based authentication system and follow the established architectural patterns.

### Core Objectives
- Centralized client information repository
- Role-based access to client data
- Department-wise client assignment
- Comprehensive client profiles with political/corporate categorization
- Activity tracking and relationship management

---

## 2. Technical Context

### Existing Architecture Alignment
```typescript
// Follows existing patterns from:
- Authentication: lib/auth.tsx (useAuth hook)
- Database: lib/supabase.ts (Supabase client)
- Components: components/ui/* (shadcn/ui patterns)
- Routing: app/dashboard/* (App Router structure)
```

### Design System Consistency
- **Theme**: Dark theme with existing color palette
- **Components**: Extends current shadcn/ui component library
- **Patterns**: Compound components, forwarded refs, CVA variants

